title: For Sale/Trade:  Kahr P380 with Night Sights
postcontent:
This is a factory refurbished, Kahr P380 with very bright trijicon night sights. Excellent condition! I got this from a dealer about a week ago. Thought I would like it but, I'd rather have something else. I have not fired or carried it. It does come with Kahr's 1 year warranty (new ones come with a 5 year). From the looks of this it looks just like a new one. My price is firm so please no low offers.

In regards to this refurbish...it was a dealer sample. I'm told there are several reasons for refurbishing...

1. During production, pistols are randomly pulled off the assembly line for quality control purposes, test fired more than just the requisite one shell for Massachusetts (maybe 200rds), examined for defects, then sold as refurbished after passing muster.

2. Police trade-ins, like the Sig Sauer "Factory Certified Pre-Owned" pistols. The pistols are examined by gunsmiths at the factory, springs replaced, function tested, etc and sold as refurbished.

3. A dealer representative's sample pistol being returned, which then goes through the same procedure as for police trade-ins.

The big difference between a refurb and a used gun, however, is that the refurb has been inspected and restored to factory specs by a factory gunsmith, who understands the pistol better than anyone.

title: For Sale:  Federal 5.56 Ammo 62gr-Green Tip--XM855--420rds
postcontent:
420rds in a Ammo Can

XM855 ammo features a 62 grain, copper jacketed, lead core, steel tip bullet. It is not armor piercing ammunition, but the steel tip does allow it to penetrate farther than other types of ammo. This bullet will attract a magnet because of the steel in the tip, and some ranges will not allow you to use it because of this. However, it will not damage the barrel of your rifle, because the steel is entirely covered by a layer of copper.

The ammunition itself is extremely high quality, and has features not seen on other ammunition of this type. This ammo has a crimped primer, reducing the chances of a blown primer stopping a semi-automatic, or automatic rifle from functioning. It also has a lacquer primer sealant and a case mouth sealant, to prevent the internal components from being compromised by moisture intrusion.

Federal offers a weather resistant ammo can containing 420 rounds of this ammunition. Composed of 14 30-round boxes containing three stripper clips of 10 rounds each, this product is ideal for those looking to store ammo long term, but who also want to be able to access and load it quickly

$425 for 420rds
